
An introduction for "Hello World!" loadable kernel module (LKM) that can display a message
in the /var/log/kern.log file ( demsg ) when the module is loaded and removed. 

Shows different way to write kernel module

method_1 :  A program to "Hello World!" loadable kernel module (LKM) that can display a message.
method_2 :  A program to "Hello World!" loadable kernel module (LKM) that can display a message.	    


Procedure to run both of the program
	$make                    //Compile the code and create a *.ko file
	$insmod first_driver.ko  //Insert the module into a kernel
	$dmesg                   //See the output logs
	$rmmod first_driver      //Remove the module from the kernel
	$dmesg                   //See the ouput log

